Uses of Class
cell2D.Filter

    • Uses of Filter in cell2D

      Subclasses of Filter in cell2D 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  ColorFilter
      A ColorFilter is a Filter that replaces the RGB value of every pixel in the original image with that of the one Color that it uses, thus turning the filtered image into a colored silhouette.
      class  ColorMapFilter
      A ColorMapFilter is a Filter that uses a Map<Color,Color> to replace some RGB values with others in the filtered image.
      Methods in cell2D that return Filter 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      static Filter Assets.getFilter(java.lang.String name)
      Returns the Filter in the list of Filters under the specified name, or null if there is none.
      Methods in cell2D that return types with arguments of type Filter 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.util.Set<Filter> Sprite.getFilters()
      Returns the Set of Filters that will have an effect on this Sprite when applied to it with draw().
      java.util.Set<Filter> SpriteSheet.getFilters()
      Returns the Set of Filters that will have an effect on this SpriteSheet's Sprites when applied to them with draw().
